Infinity PoolYoga RoomKids' PlaygroundState-of-the-art Fitness CentreHealth Club▪︎ * Payment details * ▪︎ Annual Rent 355,000 AED▪︎ one  Cheque Instalment▪︎ 5% Refundable Security Deposit▪︎ 5% Agency Fee------- Development Details -------Downtown Dubai is a large-scale mixed-use property complex and home to some of the city's most prominent landmarks including the Burj Khalifa, Dubai Mall, and Dubai Fountain. It covers an area of two square kilometres and is situated along Sheikh Zayed Road, in the heart of Dubai, mid-way between old Dubai. It is connected to the Dubai Metro via the Burj Khalifa/Dubai Mall Metro Station. Property Downtown is highly sought after, largely due to the Burj Khalifa views and access to Dubai Mall. The Burj Khalifa is the centrepiece of Downtown Dubai. At 828 metres, it is the tallest building in the world and the tallest man-made structure ever built. The Dubai Mall retains the title of the world's largest shopping mall by total area, home to around 1,200 shops in addition to in-mall attractions, such as an ice rink, an aquarium and water zoo and a waterfall, in reality, a man-made water feature. No matter which property development you choose in Downtown Dubai, a comfortable, contemporary lifestyle awaits. Central to everything Dubai has to offer, the Downtown Dubai area is well-established and likely to continue to be highly sought after in both property and leisure terms.

description: About 23 Marina Tower23 Marina in Dubai Marina is an 88-storey, 1,289 ft. tall luxury residential building. Located on Sheikh Zayed Road, it offers extraordinary views of the Marina and Dubai’s skyline. The high-rise has a total of 289 residential apartments and four below-ground levels. The construction of the building started in 2006 and was completed in 2012 by Hircon International LLC. The project built on a podium features a 6-storey entry hall with geometric flooring designs and tinted glass walls. The glass lobby area on the ground floor is complemented by the stunning outdoor swimming pool. There is a waterfall sculpture behind the concierge desk. With a structure resembling a ball-point pen, 23 Marina, Dubai boasts tastefully styled 2 and 3-bedroom apartments along with 4-bedroom duplex units. The latter have private elevators and triangular balconies with plunge pools. Other tower amenities include a children’s play pool, health club, a spa and a running track. In a NutshellType of building: ResidentialLocation: Dubai MarinaDeveloper: Hircon InternationalDate of completion: 2012Number of floors: 88Unit type: 2 and 3-bedroom apartments, 4-bedroom duplexesAmenities: Spas, fitness centres, indoor and outdoor swimming pools, jogging track. Duplexes have their own private heated Jacuzzi-style plunge pool. 3 Bedroom , 4 baths, Maids Room, Balcony, 2980 sq ft, with Marina and Golf Course View, in 23 Marina Tower. Two parking slots. High end facilities with large entrance lobby, concierge, swimming pool, gym, jogging track, children's play area, and other facilities. Well maintained, 24x7 security.

description: A one-bedroom apartment in Dubai often features a modern and luxurious design with a focus on comfort and convenience. Here’s a general description:**Living Space:** The apartment typically has an open-plan living and dining area that leads to a balcony, providing stunning views of the city skyline or nearby landscapes. Large windows allow for natural light to flood the space. **Kitchen:** The kitchen is usually equipped with high-end appliances, including a refrigerator, oven, and dishwasher. It features sleek cabinetry and often includes a breakfast bar or island. **Bedroom:** The bedroom is spacious, often featuring built-in wardrobes and en-suite bathroom facilities. It may have large windows or a balcony, enhancing the overall sense of space and light. **Bathroom:** The bathroom is designed with contemporary finishes, often including a walk-in shower or a bathtub, along with modern fixtures and fittings. **Amenities:** Many Dubai one-bedroom apartments come with access to amenities such as swimming pools, fitness centers, and communal gardens. Some may also offer concierge services and security. **Location:** Depending on the specific area, the apartment may be close to shopping malls, restaurants, and public transportation, making it ideal for both residents and investors.
